<ul><li>Matter near it would be pulled in, and <b>become very hot</b> due to compression as it nears the event horizon.</li><li>Overheating would result in clouds of hot glowing gas being thrown back into space.</li><li>A&nbsp;<b>spinning supermassive black hole</b>&nbsp;would emit&nbsp;<b>jets of hot matter</b>&nbsp;in opposite directions along its axis of rotation.</li></ul>